b'@In_A_YamChele Like Friday \xe2\x80\x9cSMOKEY TAKIN A SHIT!\xe2\x80\x9d way\xe2\x80\x94-I found a way to duck out but I\xe2\x80\x99m doing 60 in a 30, I had a parking unit in my former studio that in any other time felt Silence Of The Lambs-I-know-bodies-are-stored-here dangerous but of all days \xf0\x9f\x9a\xa8\xf0\x9f\x9a\xa8\xf0\x9f\x9a\xa8\xf0\x9f\x9a\xa8\xe2\x80\xa6cops!!!!'

b'but, sonic wise? it was what the doctor ordered: hearing reverse 808 in Revere opened up portals of possibilities in production. "wait you can change tempo MID SONG??" -----we were pretty much open'

b'by that point it was too late: MTV gave them 12 times the push as Run DMC (on a prank song at that: "Fight" started satire....Rubin made it a hit)---only true true heads (ones that loved production more than lyrics) saw Boutique for the beauty it was.'

b'I mean despite Krush Groove/Madonna tour\xe2\x80\x94-they were under radar to hip hop heads outside of NYC\xe2\x80\x94-Russ knew what he was doing: zero photos, got us hooked (to be alive for New Style/Revere 12 inch in 86) when Ill came out (cuss free) it felt like an NWA album.'
